-- McLaren’s Hamilton Wins Pole Position for Abu Dhabi Grand Prix
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-11-03T15:06:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-03/mclaren-s-hamilton-wins-pole-position-for-abu-dhabi-grand-prix.html
McLaren’s Lewis Hamilton topped
qualifying for tomorrow’s Abu Dhabi Grand Prix to claim his
sixth pole position of the season and 25th of his career.  Hamilton posted a time of 1 minute, 40.630 seconds around
the Yas Marina circuit, 0.35 seconds faster than Red Bull’s Mark
Webber. Series leader Christian Vettel of Red Bull qualified
third ahead of Williams’s Pastor Maldonado.  Lotus’s Kimi Raikkonen, McLaren’s Jenson Button, Ferrari’s
Fernando Alonso, Mercedes’s Nico Rosberg, Ferrari’s Felipe Massa
and Lotus’s Romain Grosjean rounded out the top-10 qualifiers.  Two-time defending world champion Vettel has won the past
four races to take a 13-point lead over Alonso in the standings.
Tomorrow’s race is the 18th of 20 on the season.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
